  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 12 meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Model Form — carries a structured level shortfall (achievedLevel 2, requiredLevel 3) that is addressed in the decision rationale through expert judgment and prior validation experience. The overall package decision is Accepted on the basis that the shortfall is considered bounded by compensating evidence, though the formal gap is not closed.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-cou2",
